{"1":{"w":[{"b":"0.17","h":"0.85","c":"سَبَّحَ","d":"َḥَّbَs","e":"sabbaḥa"},{"b":"0.97","h":"1.65","c":"لِلَّهِ","d":"ِhَّlِl","e":"lillahi"},{"b":"1.9","h":"2.87","c":"مَا","d":"āَm","e":"mā"},{"b":"2.3","h":"3.31","c":"فِي","d":"àِf","e":"fī"},{"b":"2.4","h":"3.62","c":"السَّمَاوَاتِ","d":"ِtَٰwَٰmَّslٱ","e":"l-samāwāti"},{"b":"3.9","h":"5.69","c":"وَمَا","d":"āَmَw","e":"wamā"},{"b":"4.4","h":"6.49","c":"فِي","d":"àِf","e":"fī"},{"b":"4.6","h":"6.83","c":"الْأَرْضِ","d":"ِḍْrَaʾْlٱ","e":"l-arḍi"},{"b":"5.4","h":"9.57","c":"وَهُوَ","d":"َwُhَw","e":"wahuwa"},{"b":"6.0","h":"10.33","c":"الْعَزِيزُ","d":"ُzyِzَʿعْlٱ","e":"l-ʿazīzu"},{"b":"7.0","h":"11.8","c":"الْحَكِيمُ","d":"ُmyِkَḥْlٱ","e":"l-ḥakīmu"}],"a":{"g":"Whatever is in the heavens and whatever is on the earth exalts Allah, and He is the Exalted in Might, the Wise."}},"2":{"w":[{"b":"0.05","h":"2.42","c":"يَاأَيُّهَا","d":"āَhُّyَaʾَٰٓy","e":"yāayyuhā"},{"b":"2.6","h":"3.54","c":"الَّذِينَ","d":"َnyِhdَّlٱ","e":"alladhīna"},{"b":"3.6","h":"4.88","c":"ءَامَنُوا","d":"۟āwُnَmāَء","e":"āmanū"},{"b":"4.6","h":"6.24","c":"لِمَ","d":"َmِl","e":"lima"},{"b":"4.9","h":"6.7","c":"تَقُولُونَ","d":"َnwُlwُqَt","e":"taqūlūna"},{"b":"6.2","h":"8.56","c":"مَا","d":"āَm","e":"mā"},{"b":"6.6","h":"9.18","c":"لَا","d":"āَl","e":"lā"},{"b":"6.9","h":"9.78","c":"تَفْعَلُونَ","d":"َnwُlَʿعْfَt","e":"tafʿalūna"}],"a":{"g":"O you who have believed, why do you say what you do not do?","ihya":"\n        <div class=\"ihya-tafsir-box\" style=\"margin-top: 15px; border-top: 1px solid #eee; padding-top: 10px;\">\n            <h5 style=\"color: #91740c; font-family: Cabin, sans-serif;\">Tafsir Al-Ihya</h5>\n            <div class=\"ihya-arabic\" style=\"font-family: IndoPak; font-size: 18px; text-align: right; margin-bottom: 10px; color: #555;\">\n                وقوله تعالى لم تقولون ما لا تفعلون المراد به الوعد الكاذب\n            </div>\n            <div class=\"ihya-english\" style=\"font-family: Arial; font-size: 14px; text-align: justify; color: #777;\">\n                Indeed, the meaning of His saying, exalted is He, \"Why do you say what you do not do?\" is the false promise [al-wa'd al-kadhib].\n            </div>\n        </div>\n        "}},"3":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.35","c":"كَبُرَ","d":"َrُbَk","e":"kabura"},{"b":"0.6","h":"1.02","c":"مَقْتًا","d":"āًtْqَm","e":"maqtan"},{"b":"1.3","h":"2.07","c":"عِنْدَ","d":"َdnِʿع","e":"ʿinda"},{"b":"2.8","h":"3.39","c":"اللَّهِ","d":"ِhَّllٱ","e":"l-lahi"},{"b":"3.6","h":"4.46","c":"أَنْ","d":"nَaʾ","e":"an"},{"b":"4.5","h":"5.37","c":"تَقُولُوا","d":"۟āwُlwُqَt","e":"taqūlū"},{"b":"5.6","h":"7.1","c":"مَا","d":"āَm","e":"mā"},{"b":"6.0","h":"7.76","c":"لَا","d":"āَl","e":"lā"},{"b":"6.4","h":"8.39","c":"تَفْعَلُونَ","d":"َnwُlَʿعْfَt","e":"tafʿalūna"}],"a":{"g":"Great is hatred in the sight of Allah that you say what you do not do.","ihya":"\n        <div class=\"ihya-tafsir-box\" style=\"margin-top: 15px; border-top: 1px solid #eee; padding-top: 10px;\">\n            <h5 style=\"color: #91740c; font-family: Cabin, sans-serif;\">Tafsir Al-Ihya</h5>\n            <div class=\"ihya-arabic\" style=\"font-family: IndoPak; font-size: 18px; text-align: right; margin-bottom: 10px; color: #555;\">\n                وقوله تعالى كبر مقتا عند الله أن تقولوا ما لا تفعلون وبما روى عن رسول الله صلى الله عليه وسلم انه قال مررت ليلة اسرى بي بقوم تقرض شفاههم بمقاريض من نار فقلت من انتم فقالوا كنا نامر بالخير ولا ناتيه وننهى عن الشر وناتيه حديث مررت ليلة أسري بي بقوم تقرض شفاههم بمقاريض من نارالحديث تقدم في العلم وبما روى أن الله تعالى أوحى إلى عيسى صلى الله عليه وسلم عظ نفسك فان أتعظت فعظ الناس وألا فاستحي مني وربما استدلوا من طريق القياس بأن هداية الغير فرع للإهتداء وكذلك تقويم الغير فرع للاستقامة والإصلاح زكاة عن نصاب الصلاح فمن ليس بصالح في نفسه فكيف يصلح غيره ومتى يستقيم الظل والعود اعوج وكل ما ذكروه خيالات وانما الحق أن للفاسق أن يحتسب وبرهانه هو أن نقول هل يشترط في الإحتساب أن يكون متعاطيه معصوما عن المعاصي كلها فان شرط ذلك فهو خرق للاجماع ثم حسم لباب الاحتساب إذ لا عصمة للصحابة فضلا عمن دونهم والأنبياء عليهم السلام قد اختلف في عصمتهم عن الخطايا والقرآن العزيز دال على نسبة آدم عليه السلام إلى المعصية وكذا جماعة من الأنبياء ولهذا قال سعيد بن جبير إن لم يأمر بالمعروف ولم ينه عن المنكر إلا من لا يكون فيه شيء لم يأمر أحد بشيء فأعجب مالكا ذلك من سعيد بن جبير\n            </div>\n            <div class=\"ihya-english\" style=\"font-family: Arial; font-size: 14px; text-align: justify; color: #777;\">\n                Indeed, great is the abhorrence [mughta] with Allah that you say what you do not do. And by what has been narrated from the Messenger of Allah, peace be upon him, that he said: \"On the night I was taken on the journey [isra], I passed by people whose lips were being clipped with shears of fire. I said, 'Who are you?' They said, 'We used to command good and not do it, and we used to forbid evil and do it.'\" The hadith \"I passed by people whose lips were being clipped with shears of fire on the night I was taken on the journey\" has preceded in the chapter on Knowledge. And by what has been narrated that Allah, exalted is He, revealed to Jesus, peace be upon him: \"Admonish yourself; if you are admonished, then admonish the people, otherwise be ashamed before Me.\" And perhaps they argued by way of analogy [qiyas] that guiding others is a branch of being guided oneself, and likewise, setting others straight is a branch of being upright [istiqamah] oneself, and reform [islah] is the purifying alms [zakat] from the minimum threshold [nisab] of righteousness [salah]. So how can one who is not righteous [salah] in himself reform another? And when will the shadow be straight if the stick is crooked? All that they have mentioned are illusions [khayalat]. Rather, the truth is that the corrupt person [fasiq] may enjoin good and forbid evil with sincere intention [ihtisab]. And its proof is that we say: Is it stipulated for enjoining good [ihtisab] that the one practicing it be infallible [ma'sum] from all sins? If that is stipulated, then it is a rupture of consensus [ijma'], and then it seals the door of enjoining good, for there is no infallibility for the Companions, let alone those below them. And concerning the Prophets, peace be upon them, there is disagreement regarding their infallibility from errors. And the Mighty Qur'an indicates the attribution of sin [ma'siyah] to Adam, peace be upon him, and likewise a group of the Prophets. And for this reason, Sa'id ibn Jubayr said: \"If none were to command good [ma'ruf] and forbid evil [munkar] except one in whom there is no fault, then no one would command anything.\" And Malik was amazed at that from Sa'id ibn Jubayr.\n            </div>\n        </div>\n        "}},"4":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.3","c":"إِنَّ","d":"َّnِiʾ","e":"inna"},{"b":"1.1","h":"1.69","c":"اللَّهَ","d":"َhَّllٱ","e":"l-laha"},{"b":"1.9","h":"2.81","c":"يُحِبُّ","d":"ُّbِḥُy","e":"yuḥibbu"},{"b":"2.7","h":"4.04","c":"الَّذِينَ","d":"َnyِhdَّlٱ","e":"alladhīna"},{"b":"3.7","h":"5.31","c":"يُقَاتِلُونَ","d":"َnwُlِtَٰqُy","e":"yuqātilūna"},{"b":"5.1","h":"7.27","c":"فِي","d":"àِf","e":"fī"},{"b":"5.5","h":"7.86","c":"سَبِيلِهِ","d":"ۦِhِlyِbَs","e":"sabīlihi"},{"b":"6.6","h":"9.62","c":"صَفًّا","d":"āًّfَṣ","e":"ṣaffan"},{"b":"7.9","h":"11.47","c":"كَأَنَّهُمْ","d":"mُhَّnَaʾَk","e":"ka-annahum"},{"b":"10.4","h":"14.13","c":"بُنْيَانٌ","d":"ٌnَٰyْnُb","e":"bun'yānun"},{"b":"12.5","h":"16.28","c":"مَرْصُوصٌ","d":"ٌṣwُṣْrَّm","e":"marṣūṣun"}],"a":{"g":"Indeed, Allah loves those who fight in His cause in a row as though they are a [single] structure joined firmly.","ihya":"\n        <div class=\"ihya-tafsir-box\" style=\"margin-top: 15px; border-top: 1px solid #eee; padding-top: 10px;\">\n            <h5 style=\"color: #91740c; font-family: Cabin, sans-serif;\">Tafsir Al-Ihya</h5>\n            <div class=\"ihya-arabic\" style=\"font-family: IndoPak; font-size: 18px; text-align: right; margin-bottom: 10px; color: #555;\">\n                اعلم أن شواهد القرآن متظاهرة على أن الله تعالى يحب عبده فلا بد من معرفة معنى ذلك. ولنقدم الشواهد على محبته فقد قال الله تعالى: \" إن الله يحب الذين يقاتلون في سبيله صفاً \".\n            </div>\n            <div class=\"ihya-english\" style=\"font-family: Arial; font-size: 14px; text-align: justify; color: #777;\">\n                Know that the evidences of the Qur'an are mutually supporting in that Allah, the Exalted, loves His servant, so it is necessary to know the meaning of that. And let us first present the evidences for His love, for Allah, the Exalted, has said: \"Indeed, Allah loves those who fight in His cause in ranks [ṣaffan].\"\n            </div>\n        </div>\n        "}},"5":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"1.17","c":"وَإِذْ","d":"ْhdِiʾَw","e":"wa-idh"},{"b":"0.53","h":"1.75","c":"قَالَ","d":"َlāَq","e":"qāla"},{"b":"1.1","h":"2.73","c":"مُوسَى","d":"ٰàَswُm","e":"mūsā"},{"b":"1.9","h":"3.89","c":"لِقَوْمِهِ","d":"ۦِhِmْwَqِl","e":"liqawmihi"},{"b":"3.1","h":"5.47","c":"يَاقَوْمِ","d":"ِmْwَqَٰy","e":"yāqawmi"},{"b":"4.1","h":"6.93","c":"لِمَ","d":"َmِl","e":"lima"},{"b":"4.4","h":"7.44","c":"تُؤْذُونَنِي","d":"àِnَnwُhdْwʾُt","e":"tu'dhūnanī"},{"b":"5.9","h":"9.43","c":"وَقَدْ","d":"dَqَw","e":"waqad"},{"b":"6.5","h":"9.97","c":"تَعْلَمُونَ","d":"َnwُmَlْʿعَّt","e":"taʿlamūna"},{"b":"7.6","h":"11.91","c":"أَنِّي","d":"àِّnَaʾ","e":"annī"},{"b":"8.9","h":"13.32","c":"رَسُولُ","d":"ُlwُsَr","e":"rasūlu"},{"b":"9.9","h":"14.62","c":"اللَّهِ","d":"ِhَّllٱ","e":"l-lahi"},{"b":"10.6","h":"15.64","c":"إِلَيْكُمْ","d":"ْmُkْyَlِiʾ","e":"ilaykum"},{"b":"12.0","h":"20","c":"فَلَمَّا","d":"āَّmَlَf","e":"falammā"},{"b":"13.","h":"21.71","c":"زَاغُوا","d":"۟āٓwُغāَz","e":"zāghū"},{"b":"15.6","h":"23.99","c":"أَزَاغَ","d":"َغāَzَaʾ","e":"azāgha"},{"b":"16.5","h":"25.22","c":"اللَّهُ","d":"ُhَّllٱ","e":"l-lahu"},{"b":"17.","h":"26.32","c":"قُلُوبَهُمْ","d":"ْmُhَbwُlُq","e":"qulūbahum"},{"b":"18.9","h":"29.55","c":"وَاللَّهُ","d":"ُhَّllٱَw","e":"wal-lahu"},{"b":"19.9","h":"30.96","c":"لَ